1
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:17,640
Mr. Fu,

2
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:19,360
can you take me out

3
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:20,000
today?

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:24,960
I...

5
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,080
I asked Yan Hong.

6
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:27,320
You don't have work today.

7
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:47,160
I'll keep Pang Jingfu busy

8
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:48,480
to make sure he won't go

9
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:50,200
to the Yinguangtang Jade Factory today.

10
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:52,120
You have some time

11
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,600
to investigate the factory.

12
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:55,920
[There must be something wrong with those workers.]

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,200
You brought me to such a remote place.

14
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:08,640
Do you want to sell me?

15
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,920
Don't you watch TV?

16
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:12,840
This place,

17
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:15,960
Reef Bar at Sunrise Dongshanhai Resort,

18
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:18,280
is hard to book a table.

19
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:20,560
You booked the whole place?

20
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,880
I just mentioned it casually.

21
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,760
I didn't expect you to be so serious.

22
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,400
Sunrise Lover's Bay.

23
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:32,000
You really are

24
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,400
all bark

25
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:33,720
and no bite.

26
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,560
Yan Hong booked it.

27
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,880
Looks like we have similar tastes.

28
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,800
This is where I

29
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,040
scattered my mom's ashes.

30
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,280
Our house was burned to ashes.

31
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:52,720
I remember

32
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:55,160
running into what I thought was the kitchen.

33
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,280
That was

34
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:59,680
the place where my mom would go,

35
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,760
but my dad never came close.

36
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,120
I chose that place

37
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:04,800
because

38
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:05,640
I didn't want

39
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,840
my mom's ashes to get mixed with dirty things.

40
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,080
But now I think

41
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,160
what I scattered into the sea

42
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:15,960
might just be some

43
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,680
remnants of pots, bowls, and utensils.

44
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,080
Sometimes I wonder

45
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,520
my only relative doesn't remember me anymore,

46
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,880
I don't think I have a reason to live.

47
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,760
But I owe a lot.

48
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,880
I owe my grandmother an explanation.

49
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:33,600
I owe...

50
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,360
I owe my master a last wish.

51
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:41,280
Anyway, there are always some inexplicable obsessions

52
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:42,280
or

53
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:43,960
responsibilities

54
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,240
that make me

55
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,720
want to die but dare not die.

56
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,480
I don't know

57
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,800
why I'm alive.

58
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:53,640
It's so weird.

59
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,680
My parents don't like me.

60
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,000
They hate me.

61
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,120
They resent me.

62
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,440
No one wants me to live.

63
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,520
But I survived.

64
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,440
I'm alive.

65
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:13,840
It's the best revenge on them.

66
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:16,640
So,

67
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,280
if you can't find someone to love,

68
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,360
then find someone to hate.

69
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,960
How can a person live like this?

70
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:27,600
Because I don't want to die so easily.

71
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,200
Why are you

72
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,600
comforting me?

73
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,080
Let's go for a walk.

74
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:03,800
Tian Yan.

75
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:04,560
Yes?

76
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,840
About that earring last time,

77
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,680
you've been wearing it.

78
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,480
Why

79
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,200
do you mention it suddenly?

80
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,920
I got it back

81
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,960
from the auction.

82
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,440
But it seems broken.

83
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,320
[I've disabled]

84
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,840
[the GPS signal system.]

85
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,080
[Even if Pang Jingfu got it,]

86
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,000
[he wouldn't find it.]

87
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,720
I'm not sure if it's from your mom

88
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,160
or your grandmother.

89
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,160
So...

90
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,440
I fixed it for you.

91
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:03,880
Happy birthday.

92
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,320
Tian Yan.

93
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,920
I didn't expect

94
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:33,080
you

95
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:35,480
to be so sentimental.

96
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,080
You're really persistent.

97
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,080
Persistent?

98
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,720
I should be the one saying that.

99
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,520
Why should a bastard lead Silver Light Hall?

100
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,640
Why does everyone think you're better than me?

101
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,600
Because I'm better than you.

102
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:49,880
You'll never understand this.

103
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,480
Fine.

104
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,000
Today,

105
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,080
I'll let you and your ability

106
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,280
die together.

107
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:41,880
Pang Jingfu,

108
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,280
why are you pretending to be a romantic?

109
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:47,240
Did your father pass this gene on to you?

110
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,120
If so,

111
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:52,080
why did he send your mother to die?

112
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,320
I got you.

113
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,720
You're mad.

114
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,320
Do you dare to say that you didn't

115
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,320
want Tian Yan to be your scapegoat at first?

116
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,440
You're a good son of your father.

117
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,520
You're born to be bad.

118
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,400
Even if you don't admit it,

119
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,560
it doesn't matter.

120
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,520
He may use me,

121
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:33,360
but he'll never make me a scapegoat.

122
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,000
Are you crazy?

123
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,320
This time,

124
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,200
I'll be the one to take your place.

125
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:39,800
Pang Jingfu!

126
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,440
Pang Jingfu!

127
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,640
Pang Jingfu!

128
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,240
The situation is not optimistic.

129
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,520
Whether he can wake up

130
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,880
depends on tonight's situation.

131
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,360
If you die,

132
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,200
I won't be able to find out

133
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,240
your evil deeds.

134
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,320
So,

135
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,040
Pang Jingfu,

136
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,760
please wake up.

137
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,040
What happened? How did you get hurt?

138
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,760
I... I don't know where to go.

139
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,880
Xiao Fan, just make do for now.

140
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:10,000
You can stay here to recover.

141
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,720
Don't step out of my bedroom.

142
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,520
It seems that we have changed our identities.

143
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,800
You have a boss outside.

144
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,240
Speaking of this,

145
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,560
we just left like this.

146
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,240
Your boss won't embarrass you, will she?

147
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,160
I saw her being so fierce last time.

148
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:25,920
It's okay.

149
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,000
After all, the hostage is not lost.

150
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,960
When you get better,

151
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,840
I'm willing to go back with you.

152
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,120
Don't let your boss kill you.

153
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,800
Where are you?

154
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:10,760
Why do you act like a thief

155
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:11,920
in your own home?

156
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,880
You finally came back.

157
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,440
Who are you fooling around with?

158
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:19,640
It's none of your business.

159
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,160
Even if I die outside, it has nothing to do with you.

160
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,120
As long as you know.

161
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:24,920
You even locked the door.

162
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:26,080
Come out and make me a bowl of noodles.

163
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,360
Come out.

164
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,400
Then we'll treat him as dead.
